I would challenge one thing before writing a single line of website copy:

**Do not market Operan as an AI platform.**

The moment you do that, you enter a crowded market.

Instead:

**Market Operan as Workforce Infrastructure.**

Public-sector CIOs, CHROs, Transformation Offices, Shared Services Centers, and Enterprise PMOs do not wake up thinking:

> "I need an agent swarm."

They wake up thinking:

> "I need to process 300,000 requests without doubling headcount."

or

> "I need to preserve institutional knowledge."

or

> "I need to reduce operational costs by 40%."

or

> "I cannot hire enough specialists."

The website must therefore sell outcomes, not technology.

